tion system. The book's genre spans fiction/non-fiction, autobiography and social theory.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAccident victims. 0aFractures. 0aHealthxPhilosophy. 0aHealthxSocial aspects. 0aMedical jurisprudence. 0aMedicinexHistory. 0aSocial medicine. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978186134937840uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847422361?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847422361423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847422361/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013